Club-Mate is a German club beverage that basically consists of lightly-carbonated, lightly-sweetened, heavily caffeinated tea. Somehow it was adopted by the German and Austrian hacker scene as their official staying-up-late-and-coding beverage. Open Mate is the first hacked Club-Mate. Thanks to open sourcing the resipes a lot of variants exist (see below).

=More Information=

#Hackerspace [http://www.hackpittsburgh.org/ HackPittsburgh] has created [http://www.hackpittsburgh.org/brewing-open-mate-soda Open Mate]
#Rochester-based [http://www.interlockroc.org/ Interlock-Hackerspace] derived a more lemonlike variant called [http://www.interlockroc.org/2010/04/17/open-mate-beta-2/ Open Mate Beta 2]
#San Francisco Hackerspace [https://www.noisebridge.net/wiki/Noisebridge Noisebridge] derived a ginger-beer called [https://www.noisebridge.net/wiki/Sudo_pop Sudo Pop]
#Following [http://www.make-digital.com/make/vol23?pg=43#pg43 MAKE-Magazine] [http://blog.makezine.com/archive/2010/08/how-to-homebrew-club-mate.html Dave-Mate] has come closest to the original beverage.

